{
  "stem": "6009.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they transported us to another camp not very far away by train.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there, form all the camps in Germany, all the Jewish boys came over there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were thousands of Jewish boys from the Polish army.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there they made three transports, one to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That means that Warsaw was the capital Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That time was it to.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The Germans gave us small Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And one side of Poland they took to Germany to connect it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And one part went to Russia, because Russia fell over, too.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the center was the little Poland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The one was transported to Poland, the one was transport to Russia, and one to transport to Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I was on the side, what belongs to Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they registered everybody there the name I think and took a couple days.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they brought down a regular beautiful luxury train, and set us in, and gave us food and everything, and gave us a paper that we are released from prison.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So who could think that we're not going home?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Nobody could think of it that way.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we came in the middle of the night.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They stopped the trains, that everybody should get out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the Gestapo staying waiting for us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They take us to Treblinka.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In there they tried the-- the Jewish-- Jewish-- no, how is it said-- the Jewish federation in Lublin that was close to Treblinka.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they should buy out the prisoners.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Otherwise, they're going to kill them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they took them in the town.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they killed a group every day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Finally, we got in connection with the Jewish federation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they let out-- at first they let out the boys from Lublin, must have had families in Lublin.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they took them out.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
